begin_memory_text: I asked him if he was a big movie fan because he was wearing a zootopia shirt and had a Spielberg book on his counter. He said he was, and that zootopia was his favorite movie.
middle_memory_text: We talked about some other movies we liked, and about Lord of the Rings and the video game. We also talked about the Hobbit films and some audiobooks.
end_memory_text: We talked about his trip to New Zealand. He got to see the movie sets, and to hike and he had to watch Lord of the Rings as a prerequisite for the trip.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will go well. I feel like I'm mostly recovered from my cold, and I can begin to clean up the house and get back on track from all the things that slipped while I was sick. I think with Kate going back to school, I will also have a chance to get caught up.
critical_positive: We both had some similar interests in movies, Harry Potter, and Lord of the Rings. We were able to chat a lot about these interests, and I think I could have talked longer to him about those things. We both clearly are very interested in movies and the making of movies, so it was fun to chat with him about that.
critical_negative: I think in the beginning, before we landed on something to really talk about, we were sort of feeling out each other and the conversation topics. It didn't really pick up until we started talking about movies that we both liked. We seemed to be of very different age brackets, so I wasn't sure if we would have anything in common.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation, my partner and I enchanted pleasantries and discussed our current hobbies and interests. This included things like my love of 3D-printing and how she had recently obtained a CriCut.
middle_memory_text: At this point we began discussing specific movies. I suggested watching Jurassic Park due to its lack of blood, and then my partner revealed that she is a big fan of Lord of the Rings, which led to an in-depth discussion of the film.
end_memory_text: The final minutes of our conversation were spent discussing Lord of the Rings in earnest. We talked about everything from how it compared to the Hobbit Trilogy to my visit to New Zealand and the exploration of specific LOTR filming locations.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to go relatively well. I have an online interview which I am going to complete (and I hope will result in me earning a little bit of spending money). In addition, later this week I am going to run a Dungeons and Dragons game for my friends, which is both scary and exciting.
critical_positive: I think what worked well was the fact that my partner and I found something in common with one another (our interest in Lord of the Rings) and then discussed it in-depth. This resulted in a very enjoyable conversation in which both of us were wholly invested in what the other had to say.
critical_negative: To be entirely honest, nothing really stood out to me as not working well. I found the conversation enjoyable and didn't feel like either of us spent too much time talking. In addition, the content of the conversation was very interesting to me (and I think for my partner too) so I have no complaints regarding what was discussed.
